WEBVTT

00:03.837 --> 00:05.755
accessible to everyone in this country.

00:05.880 --> 00:08.591
You need to start bringing
in venture capital firms.

00:08.800 --> 00:11.720
Hello, Don. Elizabeth Holmes.

00:11.970 --> 00:13.596
And when Larry Ellison came to you

00:14.014 --> 00:16.891
with his vision for how Oracle
could organize data,

00:17.017 --> 00:19.894
- you said, "How much do you need?"
- I want you to meet Larry Ellison.

00:20.145 --> 00:21.980
If you want this, you gotta fight!

00:22.105 --> 00:24.315
That's what it takes
to run a billion-dollar company.

00:24.607 --> 00:26.776
- Is that what you really want?
- Yes!

00:26.901 --> 00:28.778
What are you willing to do
to get it?

00:29.571 --> 00:32.282
- We faked the demo.
- Don't tell anyone else.

00:32.532 --> 00:37.328
Our series B round
closed at $165 million.

00:37.537 --> 00:40.248
I'm gonna change the world!

01:33.968 --> 01:36.763
What were you doing in India,
"Mr. Balwa--

01:36.846 --> 01:39.849
It's Balwani.
And I've actually got somewhere to be.

01:40.225 --> 01:41.851
- Oh. Where?
- I'm buying an iPhone.

01:42.769 --> 01:43.770
A what?

01:44.395 --> 01:45.438
It's new.

01:45.563 --> 01:47.899
And why do you need another phone,
Mr. Balwani?

01:48.024 --> 01:49.234
What is the phone for?

01:50.902 --> 01:53.154
- Is this funny to you?
- No, sir.

01:54.322 --> 01:55.406
What's your occupation?

01:56.699 --> 01:59.494
I started a company and...
and I sold it, so...

01:59.619 --> 02:01.913
Going to ask you again,
what is your occupation?

02:04.499 --> 02:05.625
I don't have one.

02:13.633 --> 02:14.634
- Yeah!
- Come on in!

02:17.512 --> 02:20.014
I fucking love Steve Jobs!

02:23.768 --> 02:24.894
Whoo-hoo!

02:25.019 --> 02:28.273
I got the first one. Yeah!

02:28.731 --> 02:30.066
Whoo!

02:30.275 --> 02:31.985
Yeah!

02:32.277 --> 02:34.237
Whoo!

02:34.821 --> 02:36.197
Yes!

02:37.740 --> 02:38.908
Yes!

02:39.242 --> 02:40.660
Whoo!

02:49.043 --> 02:51.921
You designed the iPhone.

02:52.505 --> 02:55.425
I'm-- I'm so starstruck right now.

02:55.675 --> 02:57.594
Well, I can't take all the credit.

02:58.094 --> 02:59.762
- And Steve wouldn't let me.

03:00.555 --> 03:02.390
But I did make it prettier to look at.

03:03.183 --> 03:05.727
See that's the thing
Steve really understood.

03:06.060 --> 03:07.145
You can have all the right tech

03:07.228 --> 03:09.105
on the inside,
but without the right look--

03:09.397 --> 03:10.982
- None of it matters.
- Yeah. Exactly.

03:11.149 --> 03:12.609
That's my weakness.

03:12.817 --> 03:14.944
I... I never think about
what things look like.

03:16.112 --> 03:17.780
I can see that.

03:18.948 --> 03:20.033
Oh. No. You don't...

03:21.159 --> 03:22.493
you don't like what I'm wearing?

03:22.702 --> 03:25.079
You should just dress more like a CEO.

03:26.956 --> 03:31.252
I... When I was with Mark Zuckerberg
at the photoshoot for <i>Ink,</i>

03:31.419 --> 03:34.839
he was wearing soccer sandals, flip-flops.

03:35.131 --> 03:39.302
Yes, but you are a woman.
If you wear soccer sandals to work,

03:39.469 --> 03:41.554
everyone would think
that you're having a mental breakdown.

03:41.679 --> 03:44.057
Yeah, I just don't wanna waste my time
picking out what I'm gonna wear.

03:44.933 --> 03:46.059
It's not a waste of time.

03:46.434 --> 03:47.810
For you. You're a designer.

03:48.478 --> 03:52.732
Listen, how you present yourself
to the world is your identity.

03:53.483 --> 03:55.068
It's-- it's your armor.

03:55.818 --> 03:57.195
You're a good person,

03:57.654 --> 03:58.696
I'm rooting for you.

03:59.489 --> 04:00.490
Honestly,

04:01.032 --> 04:04.869
it's just really exciting to me
that you're a young female CEO

04:04.994 --> 04:06.996
instead of a cocky little boy
in a sweatshirt.

04:12.377 --> 04:14.003
Yeah, well...

04:14.379 --> 04:17.465
what do I have to do
to convince you to work here?

04:19.092 --> 04:22.262
Avie Tevanian joined our board,
and he's a big fan of you.

04:22.720 --> 04:23.721
I love Avie.

04:24.389 --> 04:28.476
He said that you'd lose 15,000 shares
of Apple stock if you left.

04:31.354 --> 04:32.480
It's my retirement.

04:33.398 --> 04:35.275
- I got a wife, I got kids.
-Yeah.

04:36.067 --> 04:38.778
But the outsiders have
to stick together.

04:39.821 --> 04:41.155
That's how we change the world.

04:47.370 --> 04:48.371
Seriously though,

04:49.038 --> 04:51.082
your company
has momentum now.

04:51.666 --> 04:55.211
And when the board starts smelling money,
they're gonna get tough on you.

04:56.629 --> 04:57.630
Watch your back.

05:02.051 --> 05:04.304
Why the fuck do you want a car
that doesn't make any noise?

05:04.470 --> 05:06.681
It's a Prius, Sunny.
It's what everybody is driving.

05:06.931 --> 05:08.308
Why do you even need a new car?

05:08.808 --> 05:10.143
I like driving you.

05:25.199 --> 05:26.451
It's not even real leather.

05:27.702 --> 05:28.703
I like it.

05:31.581 --> 05:33.916
You know, I'm looking into
this computer science grad program

05:34.000 --> 05:35.126
at Stanford.

05:35.376 --> 05:38.004
I'm thinking of going back
to school again. What do you think?

05:38.713 --> 05:40.298
Do you think my board respects me?

05:41.883 --> 05:43.551
Sure. Just keep making them money.

05:45.928 --> 05:46.929
Could they fire me?

05:47.764 --> 05:48.806
From my own company?

05:49.891 --> 05:50.975
Of course they can.

05:51.684 --> 05:53.895
You took money from VCs. They own you.

05:58.816 --> 06:00.693
Hey. Do you have any questions?

06:03.529 --> 06:05.156
The demo cars don't lock.

06:05.239 --> 06:06.574
-<i>My name's Bruce.</i>

06:06.657 --> 06:07.867
<i>If you have any questions, let me know.</i>

06:09.160 --> 06:10.870
Ugh! I have to get this.
It's Larry Ellison.

06:17.460 --> 06:18.503
Hey, Sunny,

06:19.087 --> 06:21.089
we should go out,

06:21.672 --> 06:23.216
like, on a date or something.

06:24.550 --> 06:25.551
Okay.

06:28.930 --> 06:30.223
Is she taking a call in there?

06:31.224 --> 06:32.225
It's private.

06:34.685 --> 06:37.188
<i>I know you're not</i>
<i>much of a reader, but Elizabeth</i>

06:37.271 --> 06:41.734
was just profiled in <i>Ink </i>magazine's
30 under 30 with Mark Zuckerberg...

06:42.402 --> 06:43.444
who made Facebook.

06:44.112 --> 06:46.406
Is that the thing
where single people put their pictures up?

06:46.531 --> 06:48.032
My stepson is on that.

06:49.033 --> 06:50.201
Hey, not a big deal,

06:50.284 --> 06:53.371
but has Elizabeth received any emails
from Richard lately?

06:53.454 --> 06:56.582
No. Why would Richard
be emailing Elizabeth?

06:57.417 --> 06:58.418
Well,

06:58.543 --> 07:01.671
this is kinda silly actually,
but I think he was hurt

07:01.796 --> 07:03.881
that she didn't contact him
for advice on her company,

07:03.965 --> 07:06.884
you know, since his company
also invents biomedical devices and...

07:07.135 --> 07:08.678
- It made him a little angry.
- What?

07:09.303 --> 07:12.473
He was mad
she didn't call him for advice?

07:12.598 --> 07:14.767
Well... yeah.

07:15.184 --> 07:16.811
He's been researching
what she's doing.

07:16.936 --> 07:19.147
I think he might be trying to have
a little fun with her company.

07:19.230 --> 07:20.815
"A little fun with her company." What?

07:21.065 --> 07:23.401
He applied for a patent.
I don't really understand it,

07:23.484 --> 07:26.654
but I think he wants her to buy him off,
you know, just for fun.

07:27.822 --> 07:30.158
So, your husband
has been secretly researching

07:30.241 --> 07:33.369
my daughter's company
so he can make money off her?

07:33.494 --> 07:35.538
My 23-year-old daughter?

07:36.581 --> 07:38.207
Well, you don't have
to make it sound so bad.

07:40.168 --> 07:41.252
Mrs. Holmes.

07:42.170 --> 07:44.881
Wait. Mrs. Holmes!

07:46.382 --> 07:47.717
Mrs. Holmes!

07:49.051 --> 07:50.052
Richard!

07:51.137 --> 07:52.722
- Richard!
-Yes?

07:53.598 --> 07:54.599
Richard!

07:57.059 --> 07:59.979
Hello, Noel.
You look like you need a glass of water.

08:00.104 --> 08:01.481
What did you do to Elizabeth?

08:01.606 --> 08:03.733
Richard. Richard!

08:04.692 --> 08:05.693
Oh, God.

08:05.943 --> 08:07.528
You're trying to mess
with Elizabeth's company?

08:08.196 --> 08:10.281
Richard. Everybody, be nice.

08:10.448 --> 08:12.533
There's nothing for you
to worry about,

08:12.700 --> 08:13.868
- Noel.
- He's just having fun.

08:14.160 --> 08:17.371
I'm a businessman.
I think she's got a great idea.

08:17.622 --> 08:18.831
I wanna be a part of it.

08:19.248 --> 08:23.586
So, I looked into what she's going
to need, and I invented a mechanism

08:24.128 --> 08:26.172
that will alert doctors
when their patients

08:26.297 --> 08:29.217
have an abnormal blood test.
If she ever wants to put

08:29.300 --> 08:31.219
a blood-testing device
in someone's home,

08:31.302 --> 08:34.472
- she'll have to license my invention.
- Buy you off.

08:36.307 --> 08:38.267
Your words, not mine.

08:38.476 --> 08:40.853
- You're sick.
- If she'd called and asked my advice,

08:41.020 --> 08:43.231
I would've told her.
Things like this can happen.

08:43.481 --> 08:46.317
- You know what? Can I get anyone coffee?
- You're a tiny man.

08:49.487 --> 08:53.991
Oh, stop being such a nice little WASP
and tell me to fuck off, Noel.

08:55.117 --> 08:56.077
Fuck off!

08:56.744 --> 08:57.912
No, you fuck off.

08:57.995 --> 09:01.582
Fuck you! Fuck you! Fuck you!

09:10.341 --> 09:12.343
- You said that to him?

09:12.426 --> 09:15.680
- Your mom used the F word.
- I said it a couple of times.

09:18.015 --> 09:19.058
Thank you. I...

09:19.392 --> 09:22.311
I haven't heard about
any patent applications.

09:22.478 --> 09:25.398
- He's... he's bluffing.
- I'm never speaking to Lorraine again.

09:25.523 --> 09:28.150
- They both can fuck off!
- Oh, my gosh.

09:31.779 --> 09:33.447
-<i>Mm! Shit!</i>
- What?

09:34.490 --> 09:36.534
I spilled my coffee. Oh, shit.

09:37.034 --> 09:38.744
Doesn't the Prius have a cup holder?

10:09.358 --> 10:11.277
Hey, Bridget Jones.

10:12.570 --> 10:14.822
I thought we were meeting with the board.

10:15.239 --> 10:17.199
Girl, that cannot be
what you are wearing.

10:17.533 --> 10:21.037
-Oh, I... I spilled my coffee.
-Oh, God.

10:22.830 --> 10:25.166
I've been meaning to ask you,
I still haven't received dimensions

10:25.333 --> 10:26.334
for the prototype.

10:26.751 --> 10:27.752
Oh...

10:28.753 --> 10:29.754
Yeah.

10:30.379 --> 10:33.299
-Elizabeth. We're up here.
- Hi, Don.

10:33.549 --> 10:37.011
Hey. Sweetheart, you're so skinny.
You should eat something.

10:46.395 --> 10:50.483
Come on, baby.
Come on, baby. Come on...

10:51.942 --> 10:52.902
Fuck.

10:54.278 --> 10:55.363
Ceiling between the channels...

10:55.446 --> 10:57.406
Sucks. Yeah.

10:57.990 --> 11:00.534
Uncontrolled mixing is gonna kill
result accuracy.

11:00.868 --> 11:01.869
So, you agree?

11:02.203 --> 11:03.913
Well, it's not ready for the Pfizer trial.

11:04.121 --> 11:05.456
No.

11:07.708 --> 11:08.709
I'll tell her.

11:09.377 --> 11:11.712
I mean, she'll get it.
It's-- it's-- it's people.

11:11.837 --> 11:13.214
We can't test this on people.

11:14.423 --> 11:15.424
No.

11:16.008 --> 11:17.134
They're all waiting for you.

11:17.343 --> 11:18.844
-Wow.

11:21.305 --> 11:22.348
Oh, wow.

11:25.017 --> 11:26.477
Hi. Hi, guys.

11:27.645 --> 11:28.729
Thanks for coming.

11:30.231 --> 11:31.232
Wow.

11:39.490 --> 11:42.618
It's great that, uh,
we've got the board here.

11:42.868 --> 11:46.706
The... This new location, new space.

11:47.248 --> 11:48.999
Speak up! We can't hear you.

11:53.963 --> 11:56.090
- So, we have some...

11:59.802 --> 12:01.929
- We have...

12:02.513 --> 12:04.223
We have some exciting
new developments.

12:07.143 --> 12:10.646
Including Ana Arriola, who has been
with us for a few months.

12:10.813 --> 12:13.858
And Ana and Avie Tevanian
know each other from Apple.

12:14.775 --> 12:17.361
That's right. We stole her from Apple.

12:21.157 --> 12:22.950
Has there been any progress
on the prototype?

12:23.492 --> 12:26.370
'Cause I know an engineer
who can come in and really ramp things up.

12:26.495 --> 12:30.416
- His name is Brendan Morris.
- Thank you, but we are full steam ahead.

12:34.920 --> 12:36.589
What do you think
they're talking about?

12:38.257 --> 12:42.553
He's worried about the Novartis contract.
Avie says it hasn't come through.

12:42.803 --> 12:46.182
Well, tell him that... that we have
plenty of pharmaceutical interest.

12:46.599 --> 12:48.434
Well, I haven't seen any of the contracts.

12:52.313 --> 12:55.357
I mean, nobody's talking about it
except Avie, but he'll bring it up.

12:55.566 --> 12:58.986
I don't know how long he'll listen to me,
but what do you want me to do?

12:59.069 --> 13:00.321
I need friends on the board.

13:00.613 --> 13:02.114
Well, of course, I'm there for you.

13:04.200 --> 13:05.785
You know, I... I've been thinking, um...

13:06.869 --> 13:08.579
when we get into this new office space,

13:09.455 --> 13:12.416
we should... you should come on as--
as a consultant.

13:12.625 --> 13:15.544
- I'm already a consultant.
- Right. But it will be more formal, like,

13:15.669 --> 13:17.963
you would have your own office and salary.

13:20.508 --> 13:23.052
Oh, that... that sounds perfect.

13:24.178 --> 13:25.971
-Elizabeth.
- Hi.

13:26.639 --> 13:27.723
Hi, Avie.

13:28.057 --> 13:31.769
I was... I was wondering,
is... is there any new about Novartis?

13:34.188 --> 13:37.566
Uh, unfortunately, we just got word
that it's not going to work out.

13:38.234 --> 13:39.318
Oh...

13:40.402 --> 13:42.613
Really? What happened?
I thought you said the contracts

13:42.738 --> 13:46.033
- were in the final stages.
- It's complicated.

13:47.368 --> 13:50.871
But I'd like to... I'd like to really
focus right now on the new space.

13:50.996 --> 13:53.874
Yeah. I'm just...
The projection's building

13:53.958 --> 13:57.378
the revenue from the Novartis deal.
Should... should we even be looking

13:57.461 --> 13:59.213
at this space if we don't
have that revenue anymore?

13:59.922 --> 14:02.550
Well, we're finalizing contracts
with Pfizer.

14:04.051 --> 14:05.803
- You are?
- Yep.

14:07.638 --> 14:09.557
I read the information you sent out,
and you haven't had

14:09.682 --> 14:12.726
a successful validation study
with actual patients yet.

14:13.352 --> 14:14.687
Well, that's a formality.

14:15.229 --> 14:16.939
Validating if the machine works
is a formality?

14:17.606 --> 14:18.607
Elizabeth.

14:20.526 --> 14:22.987
Look, I'm here to help you.

14:24.071 --> 14:26.490
That's why you have a board. To help.

14:27.908 --> 14:31.161
My father was an entrepreneur,
I understand there are ups and downs.

14:31.328 --> 14:34.248
Yeah, I've... Well, we have plenty of...
pharmaceutical interest,

14:34.331 --> 14:36.208
- including Pfizer, so...
- Yeah, but are you going through

14:36.292 --> 14:38.586
with the Pfizer trial?
Because Ana told me...

14:38.669 --> 14:39.670
You talked to Ana?

14:40.129 --> 14:41.630
Well, she said she hasn't seen
the device yet.

14:41.755 --> 14:43.007
She hasn't even gotten dimensions
for it.

14:43.090 --> 14:44.508
If you wanna know, you just...
You can ask me.

14:44.592 --> 14:47.928
- I am asking you. That is what I'm doing.
- We are going through with the trial.

14:49.889 --> 14:51.307
You're going forward
with the Pfizer trial?

14:51.473 --> 14:52.683
Yes, we are. We are ready.

14:54.977 --> 14:56.812
Ah, you know, if you...
if you'll excuse me,

14:56.896 --> 14:58.439
I have to... I have to go talk to Don.

14:58.939 --> 15:00.441
Wait, wait. Your...

15:03.777 --> 15:04.778
Your...

15:10.451 --> 15:12.578
We need to find out which employees
are talking to each other.

15:14.580 --> 15:17.249
How should I...
How do you want me to do that?

15:17.541 --> 15:20.127
Uh, I don't know. Friend them
on Facebook, and then find out

15:20.252 --> 15:21.295
who's friends with each other.

15:21.545 --> 15:24.506
Friend every employee in the company
on Facebook to spy on them?

15:24.590 --> 15:26.091
That's what I said, okay?

15:26.926 --> 15:28.177
Also...

15:30.137 --> 15:32.139
I searched for Richard Fuisz.

15:32.932 --> 15:34.016
The IT guys found this.

15:35.434 --> 15:38.979
They said it was randomly sent
to info@theranos.com, the general email.

15:39.772 --> 15:42.691
So, apparently, he just patented an alert
for a home blood testing device

15:42.775 --> 15:44.360
and they think you might have
to buy him out.

15:44.610 --> 15:46.111
I need to get legal on the phone.

15:46.362 --> 15:47.696
I need to hire a security team,

15:47.821 --> 15:49.114
and no one knows about this, okay?

15:56.288 --> 15:58.165
Oh, should I come back or...

15:59.583 --> 16:01.085
Do you want a... a shirt?

16:01.251 --> 16:02.336
It's okay.

16:08.258 --> 16:09.259
Fuck.

16:17.601 --> 16:18.727
Yes.

16:20.270 --> 16:21.522
Yes, but would you be willing...

16:22.940 --> 16:24.066
Hi, sorry.

16:26.443 --> 16:28.570
- I ordered for you.
- No, that's not what I'm saying at all.

16:29.071 --> 16:30.072
Soba noodles

16:30.155 --> 16:33.158
with miso-infused,
locally grown pumpkin.

16:34.201 --> 16:35.202
Like what?

16:36.203 --> 16:38.163
- A pumpkin patch?
- Yes, that should not be a problem.

16:38.330 --> 16:40.249
I look forward to talking after Nashville.

16:41.333 --> 16:44.253
Yeah. Okay. Bye. Yeah. Bye.

16:46.422 --> 16:47.423
Pfizer?

16:47.506 --> 16:50.134
Yeah, I'm...
I'm going ahead with the validation study.

16:51.510 --> 16:54.513
With cancer patients?
You're ready to test it on people?

16:55.889 --> 16:58.183
It's just a trial.
That's... Everybody does trials.

17:00.185 --> 17:01.270
What?

17:03.939 --> 17:05.190
You're 40 minutes late.

17:05.983 --> 17:09.153
I just found out that Richard Fuisz,
my neighbor growing up,

17:09.903 --> 17:12.364
is trying to get me to buy
a patent off of him.

17:12.489 --> 17:15.951
Avie Tevanian was asking
about our cash flow at the site,

17:16.035 --> 17:19.371
so I had to show him that we're moving
on the pharmaceutical contracts.

17:20.080 --> 17:23.000
So, I had to say yes to Pfizer,
and... I don't... I don't want this.

17:23.167 --> 17:24.251
It's okay. You can leave it.

17:27.963 --> 17:29.631
Can you get off your phone?
We're eating.

17:30.007 --> 17:32.134
I can't... I can't do this.
I have to get back to the office.

17:32.259 --> 17:33.927
- Then I'll come with you. I'll help.
- No.

17:34.720 --> 17:38.015
- "No"? Just "no"?
- I don't want them to think

17:38.140 --> 17:39.433
that I need my boyfriend's help.

17:39.516 --> 17:41.185
No one knows I'm your boyfriend.

17:42.227 --> 17:43.729
No one knows who I am.

17:43.896 --> 17:45.481
I can't do one thing wrong.

17:46.899 --> 17:49.443
I can't give them one reason
to doubt me.

17:49.943 --> 17:53.113
Or I will lose my company.
They will take it away, okay?

17:53.280 --> 17:54.490
All right, I'll see you at home.

18:12.216 --> 18:13.217
Excuse me.

18:14.093 --> 18:15.094
Excuse me!

18:17.096 --> 18:18.722
This has truffle oil in it.

18:18.847 --> 18:20.849
Uh, there's no truffle oil in this...

18:20.974 --> 18:23.602
You think I don't know
what truffle oil smells like, don't you?

18:24.269 --> 18:26.730
- No, I...
- That table over there has truffle oil.

18:26.855 --> 18:28.857
And that table, and that table.

18:29.817 --> 18:32.611
I can smell fucking truffle oil
from a mile away.

18:36.740 --> 18:38.075
