28:21.991 --> 28:23.076
<i>God damn it.</i>

28:25.787 --> 28:27.497
Yeah.

28:28.248 --> 28:30.375
Hello, could you tell us
what you're working on?

28:34.212 --> 28:36.381
Obviously, we're going
in a different direction.

28:36.631 --> 28:38.925
You've repurposed
a glue-dispensing robot?

28:39.259 --> 28:41.553
Yeah. Check it out.

28:56.359 --> 28:57.736
She's not gonna tell you
what's she's gonna do.

28:57.819 --> 28:59.195
She never tells you what's she's doing.

28:59.571 --> 29:01.406
The point is, you hired another engineer

29:01.614 --> 29:03.283
to create a completely
different prototype.

29:03.491 --> 29:07.620
I-- If I may, you see,
his machine is not microfluidics.

29:07.954 --> 29:10.874
- It... He's just reprogrammed a...
- It's a fucking glue bot.

29:11.291 --> 29:13.334
If you don't like it,
then get your version to work better.

29:13.460 --> 29:15.837
Are you trying to pit us
against each other? What are you doing?

29:16.087 --> 29:18.298
What, you... you want us
to compete against an automated arm?

29:18.465 --> 29:19.758
I want something to actually work.

29:24.012 --> 29:25.847
Is this because of what happened
in Nashville?

29:30.059 --> 29:32.771
Nashville was an inspiring step forward.

29:34.814 --> 29:35.815
Are we done?

29:43.114 --> 29:44.115
What?

29:44.365 --> 29:46.910
Is this what you want,
what Brendan's doing?

29:47.410 --> 29:50.246
He's just miniaturizing a process
that already exists.

29:51.080 --> 29:56.044
It's big and ugly and it's not new.
And... and it's not your vision.

29:58.129 --> 30:00.298
I'm worried that perhaps
this is all my fault.

30:01.466 --> 30:04.469
Perhaps I answered
the consultant's questions

30:04.677 --> 30:05.762
- in the wrong way.
- Consultant?

30:07.138 --> 30:09.140
Yes, a man called Sunny,

30:09.349 --> 30:10.934
he came while you were in Nashville

30:11.100 --> 30:12.977
- and asked us questions.
- What are you talking about?

30:13.102 --> 30:14.979
- Well, he said that...
- I... when I was in Nashville?

30:15.188 --> 30:16.147
No.

30:18.441 --> 30:20.693
You did not answer
his questions wrong.

30:23.196 --> 30:25.698
I... I can't talk about this right now,
Ian.

30:27.325 --> 30:29.869
Okay. Uh, right.

30:33.873 --> 30:37.919
You can't just show up at my office.
You told them that you were a consultant?

30:38.586 --> 30:40.213
Do you want to talk about that,

30:41.256 --> 30:44.342
or the fact you're ten years away
from the promises you made to the board?

30:54.060 --> 30:55.103
How do you know that?

30:55.895 --> 30:57.313
What's your plan?

30:58.773 --> 31:00.733
Just keep everything
from the board forever?

31:05.321 --> 31:06.406
What is that?

31:07.448 --> 31:10.034
It's green juice. I bought it for you.

31:10.535 --> 31:11.536
It's healthy.

31:12.203 --> 31:14.831
If you're going to work 20 hours a day,
you need to eat healthier.

31:14.914 --> 31:16.332
So, what are saying, you think I look bad?

31:16.457 --> 31:17.500
You look like shit.

31:29.721 --> 31:31.097
Do you know why I went to your office?

31:32.891 --> 31:34.767
Because I don't like the way you treat me.

31:35.643 --> 31:36.728
How do I treat you?

31:36.811 --> 31:39.814
You dismiss me. You act like
I'm some guy hanging around.

31:40.690 --> 31:43.526
I founded a company, I ran it, I sold it.

31:43.693 --> 31:46.237
Yeah, and that really impressed me
when I was 18.

31:52.285 --> 31:54.037
You know what I saw
when I went to your office?

31:54.120 --> 31:55.121
What?

31:56.331 --> 31:58.708
No one respects you.
No one listens to you.

31:59.626 --> 32:01.544
They talk behind your back,
they make fun of you.

32:02.629 --> 32:04.088
They're laughing at you, Elizabeth.

32:05.340 --> 32:07.926
You're in over your head.
You're going to lose everything.

32:08.509 --> 32:11.304
But go ahead, keep ignoring me,
keep dismissing me.

32:15.558 --> 32:18.144
This juice is disgusting. I hate it.

32:20.855 --> 32:22.231
- Disgusting.
- Drink it.

32:23.608 --> 32:24.609
No.

32:26.486 --> 32:27.487
Drink it.

32:28.154 --> 32:29.155
No.

32:29.280 --> 32:30.865
It cost 12 dollars. Drink it,
it's good for you.

32:30.949 --> 32:33.326
- I don't care how much it cost.
- Elizabeth.

32:33.409 --> 32:35.078
Go fuck yourself, Sunny.
I don't give a fuck.

32:35.161 --> 32:38.206
Don't throw it out! Don't throw it out!

33:06.067 --> 33:07.068
Are you coming to bed?

33:54.574 --> 33:55.992
Here at Theranos...

34:01.039 --> 34:02.248
...we are developing...

34:04.751 --> 34:06.169
new technology.

34:07.837 --> 34:10.131
This is an inspiring step forward.

